data.description: Welcome to your next real estate obsession!  This stunning two-story home with 6 bedrooms and 3 1/2 baths on a finished basement offers comfort, luxury, and space for the whole family!  It truly is a gem and the homeowner has done the most to make it shine.  Walking in, you will instantly notice the polished hardwoods throughout the first floor leading to the heart of the home, that's right, the spacious kitchen featuring sleek granite countertops, an elevated breakfast bar, stainless steel appliances, massive secondary walk-in pantry or storage area off the garage, and an inviting eat-in area with bay windows overlooking the humongous backyard.  The cozy living room leads to a huge screened-in patio area overlooking the massive backyard and newly replaced steps leading down where the current owner has not only had a new fence installed around the entire area, but has also removed multiple trees, and installed a playground area that will stay with the home. This playground is a children’s delight and parents can relax while keeping an eye on them from the comfort of their home in the additional screened-in patio on the terrace level. Don't feel like going down the steps?  No worries!  The terrace level is the place to be!  This level has its own living area which can be a possible apartment for the summer college student.  With a separate living space or media room, a built-in bookshelf for the bookworm in your family, a kitchen with space for a fridge, a dishwasher, a full bathroom with a standing shower, and a sizable bedroom with a walk-in closet, what else could you ask for. Oh….did we mention the unfinished area which is perfect for a workout room or office space?  Okay!  We get it, there is a lot to say about this home, but we are not done yet, we still have to talk about the upstairs.  Each secondary bedroom is just as big as the next, and the master bedroom bathroom features a jetted tub, double vanity, and an enclosed toilet.  The full hallway bath also offers a double vanity so each of the little ones have their own space; less fighting less stress.  Lastly, the attic/5th bedroom is perfect for an office and also offers a large walk-in closet which can also double for storage.  Needless to say, this home has it all and then some. The added energy-efficient solar panels help keep the utility cost low.  Schedule a showing today, and don't forget to view the 3D Interactive Virtual Tour.
